# Scratchpad

## Current task
SMTP email sender — COMPLETE (implemented + documented, not wired)

## Plan
- [X] SmtpEmailSender (stdlib smtplib) + verify/OTP message builders
- [X] SMTP_* settings in config (default EMAIL_BACKEND remains stub)
- [X] get_email_sender ready for smtp; accounts routes still call without settings=
- [X] Docs (docs/email-smtp.md, .env.example, README) + unit tests

## Design decisions
- Stdlib only (no new deps)
- Factory supports smtp when settings passed; routes not updated yet
- OTP helper ready; OTP flow not implemented
- EMAIL_BACKEND=smtp without settings= falls back to stub with warning

## Lessons
- .cursorrules can be overwritten by concurrent agent sessions — re-read before editing, merge don't clobber
- App Platform does NOT support volumes — document ephemeral SQLite clearly
- Hatch force-include of missing static/dist breaks local installs — copy dist post-pip in Docker instead
- Colima must be started before docker build on this machine
- Spokenly MCP may be unavailable; supercoder says NEVER ASK — proceed autonomously
- FastAPI union StreamingResponse|JSONResponse needs response_model=None
- Project venv is `.venv` (uv), not `venv`
- Helpers existing ≠ wired — always verify call sites
- EventSource cannot send Authorization — use ?token= or session cookie for SSE
- CORS allow_credentials cannot pair with allow_origins=*
- Global agent skills live in 4 dirs: ~/.claude/skills, ~/.agents/skills, ~/.config/opencode/skills, ~/.cursor/skills — keep copies in sync (verify with shasum). supercoder rewritten to v5 (98 lines, evidence-based verification, anti-rationalization table)
